Welcome to UnityCarTest poject

Pre-requisites to compile this solution
1.- iOS or android SDK installed
2.- Unity 5.5.2f installed
 
In order to modify the amount of cars on screen
You just need to modify the number of cars property in the gameManager instance located in the path game object
The file path can also be modified to the one you in the gameManager instance located in the path game object

the laps to complete and spawn time of the cars on the track comes from the file stream

The file with the data need for the project to work has to be in JSON format according to the following structure:

{
  "GameConfiguration": {
    "lapsNumber": "1",
    "playersInstantiationDelay": "8000"
  },
  "Players": [
    {
      "Name": "Pippo",
      "Velocity": "16",
      "Color": "#5adb72",
      "Icon": "http://image0.flaticon.com/icons/png/128/70/70078.png"
    },
    {
      "Name": "Michael",
      "Velocity": "27",
      "Color": "#3db2ca",
      "Icon": "http://downloadicons.net/sites/default/files/random-user-icon-15571.png"
    },
    {
      "Name": "Fred",
      "Velocity": "24",
      "Color": "#6d11f1",
      "Icon": "http://www.freeiconspng.com/uploads/cat-icon-9.png"
    }
	]
}

